MASTER DIRECTIVE: SECTION 3 - THE "MAGNUM OPUS" (STICKY SCROLL)
TO: Vibe Coding Agent
FROM: Lead Architect
PRIORITY: HIGH
OBJECTIVE: Build a cinematic, sticky-scroll project showcase.
CONTEXT: We are abandoning the traditional "Grid of Cards" layout. That is for junior developers. We are building an immersive Case Study Engine. The user must feel like they are stepping inside each project.
1. THE CONCEPT: "CINEMATIC STORYTELLING"
Instead of overwhelming the user with 6 small screenshots, we focus on 3 Flagship Projects.
The Layout: A Split-Screen design.
Left Side (The Canvas): A massive, high-fidelity visual area that acts as a "window" into the project. As the user scrolls, this area remains STICKY (pinned) to the screen. The image inside transitions smoothly from Project A to Project B to Project C.
Right Side (The Narrative): The project details (Title, Problem, Solution, Tech Stack) scroll vertically. As the "Project B" text enters the viewport, the Left Side image morphs to match it.
Psychology: This forces the client to focus on one story at a time. It implies, "I don't just churn out code; I build complete products."
2. ARCHITECTURAL BLUEPRINT (JSON)
Agent Instruction: Use this data structure. Do not hardcode HTML structure without this data backing it.
code
JSON
{
  "component_name": "ProjectShowcase",
  "interaction_type": "GSAP_ScrollTrigger_Pinning",
  "projects": [
    {
      "id": "01",
