3. TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS (STACK)
Framework: Next.js + TypeScript.
Styling: Tailwind CSS.
Animation: GSAP (ScrollTrigger).
Mechanism: We will use ScrollTrigger to detect which text section is active and update the "Sticky Visual" accordingly.
4. DETAILED IMPLEMENTATION PLAN
Step A: The Layout Structure (Mobile vs. Desktop)
Mobile: Stacked layout. Image Top, Text Bottom. Simple vertical scroll. No sticky effects (it breaks UX on phones).
Desktop (md:):
Container: flex gap-20 relative.
Left Column (Visuals): w-1/2 h-screen sticky top-0 flex items-center justify-center. This holds the mockups.
Right Column (Content): w-1/2 flex flex-col gap-[50vh]. This holds the text. The huge gap ensures we have time to look at the image before scrolling to the next one.
Step B: The "Visual" Component (Left Side)
This is the magic part.
It should contain a Laptop Frame or a Glass Card container.
Logic: It receives the activeProject index from the state.
Transition: When activeProject changes, the image inside should fade out/scale down slightly, then the new image fades in/scales up.
Background: Add a massive, blurred radial gradient behind the laptop that changes color based on the project.accent_color.
Step C: The "Content" Component (Right Side)
Each text block must be distinct.
Typography:
Project ID (01, 02) should be huge, hollow/outlined text (text-transparent stroke-white stroke-2) in the background to add texture.
Title: Bold, Heading 2.
Description: Gray-400, relaxed line-height.
Tech Stack: Use "Pill" tags (rounded-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10).
Step D: The GSAP Logic
Agent Instruction: Use useGSAP hook.
code
TypeScript
// Conceptual Logic
useGSAP(() => {
  projects.forEach((project, index) => {
    ScrollTrigger.create({
      trigger: `#project-content-${index}`, // The text block
      start: 'top center',
      end: 'bottom center',
      onEnter: () => setActiveProject(index),
      onEnterBack: () => setActiveProject(index),
    });
  });
}, { scope: containerRef });
5. UI POLISH (THE "ELITE" TOUCHES)
Agent Instruction: Do not build a boring list. Add these specific details:
Glassmorphism on the Laptop: The mockup container should have a subtle white border border border-white/10 and a deep shadow shadow-2xl.
Live Links: Add a "View Project" button that looks like a magnetic link (icon arrow 45 degrees).
Smoothness: The image transition must be seamless. Use CSS transition-all duration-500 on the image element for opacity and transform.
6. EXECUTION ORDER
Setup: Create ProjectShowcase.tsx. Define the project data array.
Structure: Build the flex layout (Left Sticky, Right Scroll).
State: Create [activeProject, setActiveProject] = useState(0).
Binding: Connect the Left Side image source to projects[activeProject].image.
Triggers: Implement the GSAP ScrollTriggers to update the state as you scroll.
Style: Apply the Tailwind polish (gradients, typography, borders).

